Dear Nick, Andrew, Aliya, All
we run 300M toys by jobs with 25K toys to evaluate a combined significance for all SRs and two years in dimuon excess analysis using command:
combine -d combined.txt -M HybridNew --LHCmode LHC-feldman-cousins --clsAcc 0 --singlePoint mu_sr1_2017=0,mu_sr2_2017=0,mu_sr3_2017=0 --saveToys --saveHybridResult -T 25000 -s -1 --setParameters mean=27.3,width=3.2 --freezeParameters mean,width,sigma --setParameterRanges mu_sr1_2017=0.0,100.0:mu_sr2_2017=0.0,100.0:mu_sr3_2017=0.0,150.0 --redefineSignalPOI mu_sr1_2017,mu_sr2_2017,mu_sr3_2017
To retrieve p-value after adding all output root files we use command:
combine -d combined.txt -M HybridNew --LHCmode LHC-feldman-cousins --clsAcc 0 --singlePoint mu_sr1_2017=0,mu_sr2_2017=0,mu_sr3_2017=0 --readHybridResult -s -1 --setParameters mean=27.3,width=3.2 --freezeParameters mean,width,sigma --setParameterRanges mu_sr1_2017=0.0,100.0:mu_sr2_2017=0.0,100.0:mu_sr3_2017=0.0,150.0 --redefineSignalPOI mu_sr1_2017,mu_sr2_2017,mu_sr3_2017 --toysFile result.root
last command took 4 days to get us p-value 2.7e-6.
We wanted to get it faster. With “hadd” we produced 10 files from all output files and
while reading them we access information to evaluate p-value by ourself.  Here a question come.
We calculated the overal p-value with following code (see comments explaining what we do in code below)
// read output files
while ((histKeyBCD=(TKey*)nextHistBCD())) {
// get pointer to HypoTestResult
RooStats::HypoTestResult* hrsp  = (RooStats::HypoTestResult*)(histKeyBCD->ReadObj());
std::string histname(hrsp->GetName());
if(histname != “data_obs”) {
//        hrsp->Print();
//  sum up the total number of generated toys
nevall=nevall+hrsp->GetAltDistribution()->GetSize();
// 1. sum up the number of events with NLL ratio > NLL ratio(data) using NullPValue()
nev = nev + hrsp->NullPValue()*hrsp->GetAltDistribution()->GetSize();
// 2. sum up the number of events with NLL ratio > NLL ratio(data) using AlternatePValue()
//         nev1 = nev1 + hrsp->AlternatePValue()*hrsp->GetAltDistribution()->GetSize();
// some printout
std::cout<<" P-value null “<NullPValue()<<” “<<  hrsp->AlternatePValue()  <<” “<GetNullDistribution()->GetSize()<<” "<GetAltDistribution()->GetSize()<<std::endl;
}
} // while
Our question is should we use NullPValue() or AlternatePValue() and what is the difference ?
We do see that
hrsp->GetAltDistribution()
is number of generated toys, but what is than
hrsp->GetNullDistribution() ?
Our script takes 20 min for run.
Thanks, Olga and Sasha.
